column1: 1,Acne,"A common skin condition caused by blocked hair follicles and oil glands, often triggered by hormonal changes.","Pimples, whiteheads, blackheads, cysts on face, neck, chest, and back.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
2,Actinic Keratosis,Precancerous skin lesions caused by long-term sun exposure.,"Rough, scaly patches on sun-exposed skin; may itch or burn.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

3,Benign Tumors,"Non-cancerous growths of the skin, including lipomas, dermatofibromas, or cysts.","Soft or firm lumps under the skin; usually asymptomatic but may be tender.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

4,Bullous,"Skin conditions characterized by blisters, such as pemphigus or bullous pemphigoid.","Large, fluid-filled blisters; painful or itchy skin; may affect mucous membranes.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

5,Candidiasis,"A fungal infection caused by Candida, often in warm, moist areas of the skin.","Red, itchy rash; white patches; often in skin folds or mucous membranes.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

6,Drug Eruption,"Skin reactions caused by medications, ranging from mild rashes to severe eruptions.","Red, itchy rash; hives; may include blisters or peeling skin.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

7,Eczema,"A chronic inflammatory skin condition characterized by itchy, red, and dry skin, often due to an overactive immune response.","Dry, itchy skin; red rashes on face, arms, legs, and other areas; may include swelling and cracking.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

8,Infestations/Bites,"Skin conditions caused by parasitic infestations or insect bites, such as scabies or bedbug bites.","Intense itching, red bumps or burrows; often worse at night.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

9,Lichen,"Chronic skin conditions like lichen planus or lichen simplex, often involving thickened, itchy patches.","Flat-topped, purple or red bumps; intense itching; thickened skin.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

10,Lupus,"An autoimmune disease that can affect the skin, often presenting as cutaneous lupus erythematosus.","Butterfly-shaped rash on face; photosensitivity; scaly or discoid lesions.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
11,Moles,Common benign skin growths made of melanocytes.,"Small, colored spots or growths; usually asymptomatic but monitor for changes.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

12,Psoriasis,"An autoimmune disease leading to rapid skin cell growth, resulting in scaly patches.","Red patches with silvery scales; itching, burning; dry, cracked skin that may bleed; nail changes.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
13,Rosacea,A chronic facial skin condition causing redness and visible blood vessels.,"Facial redness, swollen bumps, visible blood vessels, eye irritation.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
14,Seborrheic Keratoses,"Benign, non-cancerous skin growths that appear with age.","Waxy, scaly, slightly elevated brown or black lesions.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

15,Skin Cancer,"Malignant skin growths, including basal cell carcinoma, squamous cell carcinoma, and melanoma.","Asymmetrical lesions, irregular borders, color changes, growing or bleeding sores.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

16,Sun/Sunlight Damage,"Skin changes due to prolonged UV exposure, including photoaging and solar lentigines.","Wrinkles, dark spots, rough texture; increased risk of precancerous lesions.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
17,Tinea,"Fungal infections of the skin, such as ringworm or athlete’s foot.","Red, scaly, ring-shaped patches; itching; may affect feet, groin, or scalp.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
18,Unknown/Normal,"Placeholder for undiagnosed or normal skin findings with no clear pathology.","No abnormal findings or non-specific symptoms.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

19,Vascular Tumors,"Benign or malignant growths involving blood vessels, such as hemangiomas or angiosarcomas.","Red or purple growths; may be raised or flat; potential for bleeding.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

20,Vasculitis,"Inflammation of blood vessels that can affect the skin, causing rashes or ulcers.","Red or purple spots, palpable purpura, ulcers; may be painful.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00

21,Vitiligo,"A condition causing loss of skin pigment, resulting in white patches.","White patches on skin, often symmetrical; may affect hair or mucous membranes.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
22,Warts,"Skin growths caused by human papillomavirus (HPV) infection.","Rough, raised growths; may be painful or asymptomatic; common on hands or feet.",,2025-09-01 23:01:00,2025-09-01 23:01:00
